          {"left": "bei + dem", "right": "beim"},
          {"left": "von + dem", "right": "vom"},
          {"left": "an + dem", "right": "am"},
          {"left": "in + dem", "right": "im"},
          {"left": "in + das", "right": "ins"},
          {"left": "an + das", "right": "ans"}
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "rules",
        "title": "Merke dir!",
        "items": [
          "Akkusativ prepositions: durch, für, ohne, gegen, um (DOGFU).",
          "Dativ prepositions: mit, nach, aus, bei, von, zu, seit.",
          "Contractions are very common and expected in spoken German.",
          "Always use the contracted form when available: zum Arzt, zur Schule, beim Essen."
